               <head/>
               <msContents class="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh89005046">
                  <summary>1 copy of Dīvān-i Ṣāʾib by Muḥammad ʿAlī Ṣāʾib-i Tabrīzī</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="Uk_RSPA_52-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="555r"/>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20690">Dīvān-i Ṣāʾib</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20690">دیوان صائب</title>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164658930.0x000001 viaf_91000370">Muḥammad ʿAlī Ṣāʾib-i Tabrīzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" key="viaf_91000370">محمد علی صائب تبریزی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <incipit xml:lang="fa">بسم الله الرحمن الرحیم. اگر نع مد بسم الله نودی تاج عنوانها *** نکشستی تا قیامت نو خط شیرازه دیوانه</incipit>
                     <explicit xml:lang="fa">و که نه با تو میگفتم جها کقته جها کردی</explicit>
                     <colophon xml:lang="fa">تم سنه ۱۰۷۸</colophon>
                     <note>
                        <p>This manuscript is dated to ten years before Ṣāʾib's death. </p>
                        <p>The contents of the manuscript are predominanlty his ghazals (ff1v-438v) in alphabetical order, followed by his maṭāliʿ between f439v-f458v and his mutafarriqāt between f459v-f555r. </p>
                        <p>This manuscript bears the seal of <persName key="person_f8202" role="asn">Aẓhar Khān Sayyid ʿAlī</persName>, dated 1201AH. 
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <decoNote>The first double spread (f1v-f2r) is covered in a bright and multicoloured leaf and vine pattern. Three ornamented headpieces in the manuscript (on f1v, f439v and f459v). </decoNote>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
